1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:02,461
A production line stops.

2
00:00:02,461 --> 00:00:05,646
In seconds, a perfect plan becomes impossible.

3
00:00:05,646 --> 00:00:10,976
CableTwin is a living digital twin that lets the manager see before deciding.

4
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:21,065
This is the live factory twin: three cable lines, ten client orders, streaming simulated sensors - speed, temperature, tension, power.

5
00:00:21,065 --> 00:00:25,292
Fully synthetic data, running locally, completely offline.

6
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:28,995
At ten o'clock, Line 2 stops for four hours.

7
00:00:28,995 --> 00:00:39,856
Watch the engine explore seventeen thousand eight hundred fifty-six candidate schedules and keep the ten thousand four hundred forty feasible ones - live, in front of you.

8
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:51,572
A local machine-learning model, trained on six hundred eighty-seven incidents simulated by the twin itself, recommends the balanced Cost route at seventy-nine percent confidence.

9
00:00:51,572 --> 00:00:53,500
Line two's telemetry flatlines;

10
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:55,428
plant power drops in real time.

11
00:00:55,700 --> 00:01:08,396
The manager stays in command and chooses Service instead: priority orders glide to lines one and three, crews are mobilized, and projected delay falls from six hundred twenty to one hundred forty minutes.

12
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:10,748
One click approves the plan.

13
00:01:10,748 --> 00:01:18,400
Nothing is ever sent to a machine - the decision lands in an audit trail: who decided, when, on which numbers.

14
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:28,396
Behind the twin, the same deterministic engine powers the full decision view - revised Gantt, before-and-after KPIs, complete traceability.

15
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:41,552
Verified by nine automated checks, an exact exhaustive benchmark, and a dedicated five-test harness for the recommender.

16
00:01:41,552 --> 00:01:44,196
Scan the link - it runs live in your browser.
